{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"99c10d89-9bd7-5a68-ba37-37973a5b10d4","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c974577a-9478-46ee-a817-c36bf4c0759f --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field c974577a-9478-46ee-a817-c36bf4c0759f -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 961ca6d5-65fb-4719-9443-2ab4714e2549 --><!-- begin field ea17ae27-79f1-46ee-811d-cd621cd981e9 --><p><strong>Prevalence estimates of cow's milk allergy vary in the literature due to differences in diagnostic classifications, study design and outcomes, methodology, and study populations </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Luyt et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Flom, 2019</a>]<strong>. There is also a discrepancy between self-reported food allergy and confirmed true food allergy prevalence, with over-estimates in the literature for self-reported symptoms </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Burks, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Koletzko et al, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Muraro, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Flom, 2019</a>]<strong>.</strong></p><ul><li>Cow's milk allergy is one of the most common presentations of food allergy seen in early childhood, second to egg allergy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Koletzko et al, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Ludman et al, 2013</a>]. The most common presentation is mild-to-moderate non-IgE-mediated allergy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter, 2017</a>].<ul><li>Almost all cases present before one year of age, with a prevalence of between 1.8–7.5% of infants during the first year of life [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Luyt et al, 2014</a>].</li></ul></li><li>A UK prospective birth cohort study of food allergy (n = 969) in the Isle of Wight found that 2.3% of 1–3 year olds had a confirmed diagnosis of cow's milk allergy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter, 2008</a>].<ul><li>Large differences were observed between rates of perceived food allergy and confirmed allergy on objective testing including positive food challenge results.</li><li>A nested cohort study from the same dataset (n = 543 children) found sensitization to cow's milk by skin prick test in [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Dean, 2007</a>]:<ul><li>0.37% of infants less than one year of age.</li><li>0.92% of children aged 2 years.</li><li>0.55% of children aged 3 years.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>The large EuroPrevall prospective birth cohort study (n = 12,049 children from nine European countries) observed an overall incidence of double-blind placebo-controlled food challenge-confirmed cow's milk allergy of 0.54% in Europe [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Schoemaker, 2015</a>].<ul><li>The UK had the highest prevalence of non-IgE-mediated cow's milk allergy in Europe, with a prevalence estimate of cow's milk allergy of 1.28% at 2 years of age, with 56% of cases being due to non-IgE-mediated allergy.</li></ul></li><li>A meta-analysis of 42 European studies estimated the overall pooled prevalence of cow's milk allergy for all age-groups [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Nwaru, 2014</a>].<ul><li>The self-reported overall lifetime prevalence was 6%.</li><li>The self-reported overall point prevalence was 2.3%.</li><li>The point prevalence with positive skin prick testing was 0.3%.</li><li>The point prevalence with positive serum-specific IgE testing was 4.7%.</li><li>The point prevalence with positive food challenge was 0.6%.</li><li>The point prevalence with positive food challenge or clinical history of cow's milk allergy was 1.6%.</li><li>The authors noted significant heterogeneity and variable participation rates between studies.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field ea17ae27-79f1-46ee-811d-cd621cd981e9 --><!-- end item 961ca6d5-65fb-4719-9443-2ab4714e2549 -->","topic":{"id":"a5282e12-9e0e-5a93-bf1e-c47cb44993b6","topicId":"055e8853-0668-4ee8-bef5-d86e8a39b416","topicName":"Cow's milk allergy in children","slug":"cows-milk-allergy-in-children","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2019","chapters":[{"id":"e95ad3f8-8ddd-57bd-8fe1-a01a59402ca1","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fceefe8b-f1a1-54cb-add7-5660134a61f9","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ff117841-0d0c-5d1f-ad22-a2d8db741006","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0a17cde7-a3cc-580f-a5ec-e74a03694b87","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e8251ee6-b8da-567a-b543-5efa4c24f074","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5cd1ea49-3964-5480-beb